HEADWORD: Pallas
<hw>Pal"las</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧l"l⟦ait⟧s)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>Palla`s</grk>, <grk>Palla`dos</grk>.]</ety>
<fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld> <def><person>Pallas Athena</person>, the Grecian
goddess of wisdom, called also <altname>Athena</altname>,
<altname>Pallas Athene</altname> or <altname>Athene</altname>, and
identified, at a later period, with the Roman
<persfn>Minerva</persfn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

